  "type": "mcq",
  "stem": "<p class=\"stem_paragraph \">The weight of an object on Venus is approximately <span class=\"math_expression \"><span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"the fraction 9 over 10 \"></span></span> of its weight on Earth. The weight of an object on&nbsp;Jupiter is approximately <span class=\"math_expression \"><span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"the fraction 23 over 10 \"></span></span> of its weight on Earth. If an object weighs 100 pounds on Earth, approximately how many more pounds does it weigh&nbsp;on Jupiter than it weighs on Venus?</p>\n",
